stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding PCOS) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (What Is PCOS?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (PCOS is a hormonal and metabolic condition characterized by excess androgen production,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (insulin resistance, and often \(but not always\) ovarian cysts. It affects hormones,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (metabolism, fertility, and long-term health.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 600.4 Td (Diagnostic Criteria \(Rotterdam - need 2 of 3\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Irregular or absent periods \(oligo/anovulation\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- High androgens \(clinical signs or blood tests\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (- Polycystic ovaries on ultrasound) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 526.6 Td (PCOS Phenotypes \(Types\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 504.6 Td (Type A: Classic \(most common\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 488.6 Td (- All three criteria present) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 474.6 Td (- Highest metabolic risk) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 456.6 Td (Type B: Classic without PCO) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 440.6 Td (- Irregular periods + high androgens) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 422.6 Td (Type C: Ovulatory) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 406.6 Td (- High androgens + polycystic ovaries but regular periods) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 388.6 Td (Type D: Non-hyperandrogenic) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 372.6 Td (- Irregular periods + polycystic ovaries but normal androgens) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 342.8 Td (Root Causes) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 320.8 Td (Insulin Resistance \(70-80% of PCOS\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 304.8 Td (High insulin drives the ovaries to produce excess testosterone. Managing insulin is the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 290.8 Td (key to managing PCOS for most women.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 272.8 Td (Chronic Inflammation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 256.8 Td (Low-grade inflammation stimulates androgen production and worsens insulin resistance,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 242.8 Td (creating a vicious cycle.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 224.8 Td (Adrenal PCOS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 208.8 Td (About 20-30% of PCOS is driven by adrenal androgens \(DHEA-S\) rather than ovarian. Stress) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 194.8 Td (management is key for this type.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
