BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 3: Nutrition for PCOS) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (The PCOS Diet Principles) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (The goal: Lower insulin, reduce inflammation, support hormone balance.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 628.4 Td (1. Blood Sugar Balance \(Most Important\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 612.4 Td (- Never eat carbs alone - always pair with protein/fat) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 598.4 Td (- Choose low-glycemic carbs \(vegetables, legumes, whole grains\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Eat protein at every meal \(palm-sized portion\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- Don't skip meals \(blood sugar crashes spike insulin\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (- Eat within 1 hour of waking) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 538.4 Td (2. Anti-Inflammatory Focus) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.4 Td (- Omega-3 rich foods daily \(fatty fish, walnuts, flax\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508.4 Td (- Colorful vegetables and berries) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 494.4 Td (- Turmeric, ginger, green tea) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 480.4 Td (- Minimize processed foods, sugar, and seed oils) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 462.4 Td (3. Gut Health Support) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 446.4 Td (- Fermented foods daily \(sauerkraut, kimchi\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 432.4 Td (- High fiber intake \(30g+ daily\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 418.4 Td (- Prebiotic foods \(garlic, onion, asparagus\)) Tj ET
