BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (Best Exercise for PCOS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Exercise improves insulin sensitivity - the core issue in PCOS.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 628.4 Td (Strength Training \(MOST IMPORTANT\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 612.4 Td (- 2-4x per week) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 598.4 Td (- Builds muscle which improves insulin sensitivity 24/7) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Compound movements: squats, deadlifts, presses, rows) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- Progressive overload \(gradually increase weight\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 552.4 Td (Moderate Cardio) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.4 Td (- Walking: 30+ minutes daily) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.4 Td (- Swimming, cycling, dance) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508.4 Td (- AVOID excessive cardio \(raises cortisol, can worsen PCOS\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 490.4 Td (Yoga and Stress-Reducing Movement) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 474.4 Td (- Yoga: Proven to improve PCOS symptoms) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 460.4 Td (- Helps with stress and cortisol management) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 430.6 Td (Stress Management for PCOS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 412.6 Td (Stress raises cortisol which raises insulin which worsens PCOS.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 398.6 Td (- Daily meditation or breathwork \(10+ minutes\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 384.6 Td (- Adequate sleep \(7-9 hours, consistent schedule\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 370.6 Td (- Nature exposure) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 356.6 Td (- Boundaries and saying no) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 342.6 Td (- Joyful activities and social connection) Tj ET
