BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 6: Supplements & Medications) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (Evidence-Based Supplements for PCOS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (- Inositol \(myo-inositol + D-chiro-inositol, 40:1 ratio\): Improves insulin) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (sensitivity, ovulation, and egg quality. Dose: 4g myo + 100mg D-chiro daily) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (- Vitamin D: Most PCOS women are deficient. Test and supplement to optimal \(40-60) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 614.2 Td (ng/mL\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 600.2 Td (- Omega-3 fish oil: Reduces inflammation and androgens. 2-3g daily) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 586.2 Td (- Magnesium: Improves insulin resistance, sleep, anxiety. 200-400mg glycinate) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 572.2 Td (- Zinc: Supports ovulation and reduces acne/hair growth. 30mg daily) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 558.2 Td (- Berberine: Natural insulin sensitizer \(similar to metformin\). 500mg 2-3x daily) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 544.2 Td (- NAC \(N-acetyl cysteine\): Antioxidant, may improve ovulation. 600mg 2-3x daily) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 514.4 Td (Common PCOS Medications) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 496.4 Td (- Metformin: Insulin sensitizer \(discuss with doctor\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 482.4 Td (- Spironolactone: Anti-androgen for acne/hirsutism) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 468.4 Td (- Birth control: Manages periods and androgens \(doesn't treat root cause\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 454.4 Td (- Letrozole/Clomid: For ovulation induction if trying to conceive) Tj ET
endstream
